article.headline: Dartmouth 66, Brown 64
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Mike McLaren and Mike Lang each scored 18 points as Dartmouth held on to defeat Brown 66-64 Friday night. The teams were deadlocked, 24-24, at halftime. Brown (10-14, 3-7 Ivy) built a four-point lead, 39-35, on a Luke Ruscoe 3-pointer with 13:30 to go. During the next six minutes, Dartmouth (9-15, 6-5 Ivy) answered with a 21-7 run, good for a 10-point lead, 56-46, on Brian McMillan's layup in the paint. In four-minute stretch from 6:44 to 2:14, Brown's Jason Forte, who led all scorers with 28 points, went 8-for-8 from the foul line. That helped the Bears get within four, 64-60. But Dartmouth's lead stayed at five, 66-61, when Forte missed two free throws with 58 seconds left. On Brown's next possession, he had a conventional 3-point play to get the Bears within two, 66-64, with 49 seconds left. After Dartmouth misfired, Forte had a chance to tie the game with three seconds remaining, but he missed another free throw. On the night, he was 14-of-18 from the line. Also in double figures for Dartmouth was David Gardner with 13 points. McLaren was 6-of-9 beyond the arc, and hit five triples in the second half.
